<Folder><name>Scenic Points</name><Placemark><name>Hue Imperial City</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Citadel of the Nguyen dynasty (1802–1945), UNESCO. The Forbidden Purple City inside was largely destroyed in the 1968 Tet Offensive; restoration is ongoing. Perfume River boat tours to royal tombs upstream.]]></description><Point><coordinates>107.590900,16.463700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Lang Co</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Long curve of pale beach between lagoon and ocean. Best photo of the pass curling up the headland behind. Restaurants on stilts over the lagoon serve oysters straight from the water.]]></description><Point><coordinates>108.085600,16.238900,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Hai Van Pass summit</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[496 m. Hai Van Quan ('Sea Cloud Gate') is a Nguyen-era stone fortress at the saddle. Bunkers on either side from US Army occupation. Look back north for the long curve down to Lang Co; south to Da Nang Bay.]]></description><Point><coordinates>108.129400,16.198600,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Da Nang / Dragon Bridge</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[666 m steel bridge in the form of a dragon over the Han River. Breathes fire and sprays water at 9 PM Saturdays and Sundays. China Beach (My Khe) is the old American R&amp;R beach.]]></description><Point><coordinates>108.202200,16.054400,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Marble Mountains</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Five limestone hills with caves and Buddhist shrines inside. Climb 156 steps up Thuy Son or take the elevator. The marble was carted off to make tombstones for over a century; now extraction is banned.]]></description><Point><coordinates>108.262800,16.004400,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Hoi An</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[16th-19th-century trading port frozen in time. Lantern festival on every full moon — power cut, the streets lit only by silk lanterns. Tailors will make a custom suit overnight.]]></description><Point><coordinates>108.338000,15.880100,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
